# Cursor Rules — Mestia

Cross-platform desktop video downloader & media library.

## Stack
- Backend: Rust + Tauri v2 (`src-tauri/`)
- Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite 6 (`src/`)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4
- DB: SQLite via tauri-plugin-sql (`src-tauri/migrations/`)
- Sidecars: yt-dlp + ffmpeg/ffprobe (`src-tauri/binaries/`)
- Package manager: npm

## Commands
- Install: `npm install`
- Fetch binaries: `npm run fetch-binaries`
- Dev: `npm run tauri dev` (frontend only: `npm run dev`)
- Build + typecheck: `npm run build` (`tsc --noEmit && vite build`)
- Build installers: `npm run tauri build`
- No tests/linter configured; typecheck via `tsc --noEmit`.

## Architecture
- `src/context/` — ThemeContext, DownloadsContext (queue/events), DragContext
- `src/components/` — Sidebar, Settings, DownloadsPanel, Splash, Toast, etc.
- `src/lib/` — ipc.ts (bridge to Rust), db.ts (SQLite)
- `src/views/` — Downloader, Locker (library), History, Player, MiniPlayer
- `src-tauri/src/` — lib.rs (plugins/tray/commands), downloader.rs (yt-dlp), storage.rs (files/watcher/thumbnails)
- Frontend ↔ Rust via `src/lib/ipc.ts`.

## Token-saving rules
- Do NOT rewrite whole files. Edit only relevant lines; use `// ... existing code ...` markers.
- Be terse: no preamble, no flattery, answer directly.
- Read only the needed section of a file, not the whole file.
- Match surrounding code style (naming, comments, idioms).
- No unsolicited refactors — change only what was asked.
- Code comments and UI strings are in Russian (match existing codebase).
- Keep `package.json` and `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` versions in sync.

## Keep docs current
Update these docs in the SAME change that makes them wrong:
- New/removed/renamed folder or key module → update architecture map in `CLAUDE.md`, `.cursorrules`, `.context/index.md`.
- Changed `package.json` scripts → update Commands in `CLAUDE.md` and `.cursorrules`.
- Changed stack (new defining dependency: test runner, linter, state lib…) → update Stack in all three.
- Changed a core flow (download/library/auto-update) → update `.context/index.md`.
No structure/command/stack/flow change ⇒ no doc edit. Edit only wrong lines, don't rewrite.
